---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="Business Immigration Pathways" description="Business immigration programs for entrepreneurs and investors">
  <section class="page-header section-padding">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <span class="gold-text uppercase-label">Visa Services</span>
      <h1>Business Immigration Pathways</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Programs for entrepreneurs, investors, and self-employed individuals to establish or expand their business in Canada.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="visitor-visa-content section-padding">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <!-- Provincial Nominee Entrepreneur Programs -->
        <div class="glass-card content-section">
          <div class="section-icon">location_city</div>
          <h2>Provincial Nominee Entrepreneur Programs</h2>
          <p>Provinces offer streams for entrepreneurs willing to invest, establish, or operate businesses locally. Successful nominees receive a Provincial Nominee Certificate, which can lead to permanent residence. Programs vary by province.</p>
          <p><em>Contact us for more information regarding the other countries.</em></p>
        </div>

        <!-- Federal Start-Up Visa -->
        <div class="glass-card content-section">
          <div class="section-icon">lightbulb</div>
          <h2>Federal Start-Up Visa</h2>
          <p>Designed for innovative entrepreneurs who can secure support from designated venture capital funds or angel investors, with investments starting at $75,000–$200,000 CAD. Applicants must demonstrate language proficiency, business acumen, and sufficient settlement funds.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Self-Employed Persons Program -->
        <div class="glass-card content-section">
          <div class="section-icon">brush</div>
          <h2>Self-Employed Persons Program</h2>
          <p>For individuals capable of contributing to Canada's cultural or athletic sectors, with a points-based system evaluating education, experience, language skills, and adaptability. Applicants must meet a minimum score of 35 points out of 100.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Intra-Company Transfers -->
        <div class="glass-card content-section">
          <div class="section-icon">business_center</div>
          <h2>Intra-Company Transfers</h2>
          <p>Allows multinational corporations to transfer senior managers, executives, or specialized employees to Canada. The business must be operational for at least a year, with proven financial stability and a viable plan for Canadian expansion. Work permits are typically valid for 1–3 years